    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "On windows if the full filepath of a file is too long, then the message will display when opening the file in Neovim:\r\n\r\nE303: Unable to open swap file for \"very\\long\\filepath\", recovery impossible\r\n\r\nMy tests indicate that 197 characters is the limit, with 198 character filepaths causing the error.\r\nThis may be an issue for people with deeply nested file structures or long file or directory names.\r\n\r\nI imagine this is caused by the way swapfile names are generated in neovim, and the inbuilt filename limits in windows, but I haven't explored it.\r\n\r\nWill happily delete this thread if this is a known issue.\r\n\r\nThanks, Tom",
